182
00:09:58,090 --> 00:10:01,290
There are emergency exits at the end of the corridor on every floor.

183
00:10:01,290 --> 00:10:02,790
The doors are auto-lockable,

184
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:05,690
but can be opened freely from the inside.

185
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:06,690
In order to come in from outside,

186
00:10:06,690 --> 00:10:09,390
you need to use the master key to open the door.

187
00:10:09,390 --> 00:10:13,290
Which means the killer as a personnel of the hotel!

188
00:10:13,290 --> 00:10:17,290
No, because I had the master key with me.

189
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:20,090
They probably had made a spare key beforehand.

190
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:21,590
If so, the killers are...

191
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:23,390
-those two! -Huh?

192
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:26,090
We haven't done anything...

193
00:10:26,090 --> 00:10:30,990
Those two were watching TV with me from 1:30 pm to 4 pm.

194
00:10:30,990 --> 00:10:33,490
If so, then all three of you are in this together.

195
00:10:33,490 --> 00:10:35,590
Don't be ridiculous!

196
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:40,590
Either I, who couldn't get a hold of the master key, am not the killer.

197
00:10:40,590 --> 00:10:42,690
No. There is a way to come in

198
00:10:42,690 --> 00:10:45,190
through the emergency exit even without the master key.

199
00:10:45,190 --> 00:10:47,490
No. There is a way to come in

200
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:49,890
through the emergency exit even without the master key.

201
00:10:49,890 --> 00:10:51,390
What?

202
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:54,790
For instance, Mr. Shiromoto,

203
00:10:54,790 --> 00:10:57,990
when you went to check on Chizuru at 12:30 pm,

204
00:10:57,990 --> 00:11:00,990
the door can be opened from the inside.

205
00:11:00,990 --> 00:11:02,590
Then stick a pebble or something between the door

206
00:11:02,590 --> 00:11:04,790
so that it won't close completely.

207
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:08,590
After making it look like you returned to the lakeside,

208
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:10,690
you actually entered the hotel from the emergency exit

209
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:12,690
and killed Chizuru.

210
00:11:12,890 --> 00:11:15,190
No!

211
00:11:15,190 --> 00:11:17,290
He's pretty good.

212
00:11:17,290 --> 00:11:18,390
As for Miyabe,

213
00:11:18,390 --> 00:11:19,990
if Mr. Shiromoto were his accomplice,

214
00:11:19,990 --> 00:11:21,290
carrying out the murder would've been possible.

215
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:23,990
What a thing to say, officer!

216
00:11:23,990 --> 00:11:27,090
If you returned to the hotel hidden in Mr. Shiromoto's car

217
00:11:27,090 --> 00:11:31,090
and went into the hotel from the door that he had left opened...

218
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:32,890
That is enough!

219
00:11:32,890 --> 00:11:36,290
You're treating us as if we were the killers.

220
00:11:36,290 --> 00:11:38,390
Well, I don't mean...

221
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:40,890
What about you people?

222
00:11:40,890 --> 00:11:42,490
Just what do you mean?

223
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:43,990
There is a possibility

224
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:46,590
that you people have spares to the master keys.

225
00:11:46,590 --> 00:11:48,290
You could've secretly come down from the mountain.

226
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:50,690
Please don't say such silly things!

227
00:11:50,690 --> 00:11:52,390
In order to return to this hotel

228
00:11:52,390 --> 00:11:54,790
from the highlands and the lake,

229
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:57,090
it is necessary to cross the bridge over the Tani River,

230
00:11:57,090 --> 00:11:58,990
that is under construction.

231
00:11:59,190 --> 00:12:01,890
I confirmed with the workers there a while ago,

232
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:04,390
and was told that the only car that crossed that bridge

233
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:07,290
in the afternoon was Mr. Shiromoto's car.

234
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:08,390
In other words,

235
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:10,290
the people who were capable of committing the crime are...

236
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:11,990
Mr. Shiromoto,

237
00:12:11,990 --> 00:12:13,590
Mr. Miyabe,

238
00:12:13,590 --> 00:12:16,390
Minaho and Honami,

239
00:12:16,390 --> 00:12:17,590
and you, Mr. Mouri.

240
00:12:17,590 --> 00:12:20,390
Me too?

241
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:22,790
It's exactly as Officer Mito says,

242
00:12:22,790 --> 00:12:25,290
but something's not right.

243
00:12:25,290 --> 00:12:27,490
For instance...

244
00:12:27,490 --> 00:12:28,990
